President Muhammadu Buhari on Tuesday hinted on losing his voice. Buhari disclosed that he lost his voice due to cold and his hard work. The President said this during the presentation of the 2020 budget to the joint session of the National Assembly. Buhari, who was about to commence the reading of his speech, apologised to lawmakers for losing his voice and his inability to speak audibly. According to Buhari: “Before I proceed to read the details of the budget, let me apologise for my voice. “As you can hear in my voice, I have cold because I am working hard and it’s sign that I’m working hard.” Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.